comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T21:51:10.369Z",maintainer-agent,"Live evidence 2026-07-10 (first pass with PR#502 caller-aware pm next in place): 9 open items claimed 2026-07-04 by maintainer-agent (docstring umbrella pm-4ak1, gate pm-5566, + 7 module slices pm-m0uc/mswi/uxmf/uwu0/768v/2vb2/qely) sat dormant ~6 days with zero work. Effect measured: anonymous pm next callers saw 8 of them under held_by_others as apparent live lanes and they were excluded from the shared ready pool; with PM_AUTHOR=maintainer-agent the recommender steered the owner to resume pm-5566 instead of frontier work (pm-3mna). A claim-TTL/staleness signal would have surfaced these for release days earlier. Hygiene applied this pass: the 9 claims released (items stay open, statuses untouched). Foreign lanes pm-tnud (codex-agent, 07-07) and pm-92if (claude-code-agent) left alone; pm-92if release-then-reclaim sequence verified consistent, no state defect."
  "2026-07-24T06:14:22.360Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence 2026-07-24: shipped public pure/filesystem stale-work SDK scans plus advisory health integration using item and latest valid history activity, configurable default 72h. Direct human pm update <id> --status in_progress now warns when the resulting item is unassigned; --json suppresses presentation advice to preserve parseable machine stderr. Fresh packed-install acceptance observed the warning and passed health/validate. Linked 35-test item gate and full 6208-test exact 100/100/100/100 coverage passed."
